title: For Sale:  Handgun sight tool
postcontent:
I make these to pay for my ammo. Price includes shipping.

This is a "Universal sight pusher for most handguns with slides, it will adjust/remove/install rear sights and front sights.

The aluminum spacer on the bottom can be removed for tall slides and front sights.

You may need to shim the slide with a few washers to get the right height.

To prevent scuffing the slide I use 2 cleaning patches around the slide before clamping.

It has been used on,

1911's
Glocks
XD's
Sigs
M&P's

and many more...

Keep in mind some sights are machine pressed and will need to soak in penetrating oil for a day, (XD's are one of them).

Sights are almost always directional, Be sure you know which way to push the sight for removal (right to left, left to right).

Here is a link to the Gunsamerica review

http://www.gunsamerica.com/blog/an-affordable-pistol-sight-adjustment-tool/

title: For Sale/Trade:  Belgian Revolver
postcontent:
Belgian Revolver: Predates 1922 based on markings. Proofs show it is Belgian and made in the region/city of Liège. The stamp "R" means "rifled barrel", "ELG" = "Epreuvé à Liège" (proofed at the proof house of Liège). The crowned "L" may be a control stamp from the same proof house. There is no caliber stamped, but it appears to be either a .32 cal or 8mm.
It is a "black powder only" gun, otherwise there would have be a stamp representing a lion with "PV" underneath. "PV" = "Poudre Vive" (smokeless powder). It appears to be fully functional, but as with all antique arms, it is not recommended that it be fired unless completed evaluated by a qualified gunsmith familiar with antique arms. It ahas all the original finish with some use wear as shown.

The rifle in my opinion is in 95% condition, with very little use and is part of an estate being liquidated. These early rifles will probably become colectable some day being the company was sold and the plant closed ?? who knows. title: For Sale/Trade:  1939 Luger S-42 Matching Numbers
postcontent:
I have a 1939 9mm S-42 Luger made by Mauser. This was the last year Mauser made them and it is a very nice piece.  I took the picture with my iPhone so it looks a lot better than the pic.

My uncle,.. (according to the story) killed a Nazi in WW II and took this off him.  He gave it to my dad, who in turn gave it to me.  I am not a collector but I do know what it's worth.  I am selling it to let someone who IS a collector enjoy it and have a great piece of history.  I am a 1911 guy and am looking to get a Springfield TRP and 9mm EMP for carry.  That's the other reason for selling.

The numbers on the frame match the numbers on the barrel, which match the numbers on the magazine.  I have no holster.  This is a very nice pistol for someone who knows what they are buying.

No trades unless it is specifically for a Springfield 1911 TRP + cash or EMP 9mm + cash.

Thanks a bunch,
Carl

title: For Sale/Trade:  CZ 550 .308 cal Sniper Rifle w/ scope and bi-pod
postcontent: I have a very nice cz550 I always wanted a sniper rifle. so i put this beauty together. It has a solid wood stock 5 round clip, bolt action,and a 2 stage trigger. The gun itself is in perfect condition. Its only been shot around 3 dozen times. I used it for range shooting, so its not been dragged through the forest with branches and rock scraping a crossed it all day. I have moved from my country live to the city,and no longer have a good place to range shoot. so letting my treasure go. the other nice things that it has is a very nice shoulder strap which has bullet slots in it a bi-pod with two  expendable arms. a must for a good steady aim. and the mother of all scopes.(which cost almost as much as the gun.lol) Its a Springfield Armory 4-14x56 2nd gen. government model. its hard to describe but this scope has it all lens covers, shade covers wind adjusters low light recital, and so on. it being a military scope also has the muli cross hairs. when you look inside the scope you see several dashes and boxes. you use some for distance. like shooting 200 yard you have a cross hair for that. it have lines and boxes for prey. once you know how far the item is you pick the line for distance and then you pick a box for the width. say you are hunting a deer. you know a has a typical body size  so you line the dashes up till the body just fits inside the dashes and you know how far its from you and make a perfect heart shot. it also has these boxes and dashes for several animals and even has a 3inch box which i found out is used in military for head shots seeing a humans eyes are  3 inches apart. hopefully you will never need those. but you do get a cool reaction when you show that to your friends. Last but not lest it all comes in a padded gun case that can be pad locked 2 different times if desired. This is an amazing gun, and i hate to see it leave but want it to be used and not sit in a closet the rest of its life. If you have Question let me know. to buy all this today would run you just over 1,500.00 dollars and that's buying from the cheapest sites on the web. feel free to look it up your self. Cz 550's are really good guns and are well sot after. I am asking 1,000.00 obo Thanks for taking the time to look.

title: For Sale:  Ethical hunter looking for land to bow hunt
location: Im not picky, Northwest, KS, Kansas
postcontent:
Hello, my name is Chris and I am trying to find a land owner that would allow access to hunt their property. I am a extremely safe and ethical person and respect not only any land I hunt but I respect the game animals I hunt. Honestly I'm not a person with a whole lot of money.

   I am a 26 year old husband and father of three beautiful girls (4,2,1) that I put way before hunting. If money is required I could probably come up with something, but I would like to find a nice land owner to create a relationship in hopes that when my young daughters get older they could come out and create some good ol memories. I'm not looking for land to hunt every day or weekend, I just need somewhere to go in season when I get time. I believe that nothing in life is free, I have no problem helping or working on anything for any land owner willing to help me out. Like I stated before I am more or less looking for someone to begin a relationship with. Thank you and god bless.

**UPDATE** I appreciate the replying about the Kansas WIHA. I know all about Kansas WIHA and that's what my problem is. I am just getting tired of unethical hunters during whatever season. What drew the line for me was last year I and a many times before I have been shot at because of a deer, pheasant, duck or whatever. I know CL is a long shot for trying to find someone nice enough to let me hunt their land but it is worth a try for the safety of myself. All of these out of state hunters ruin it for a lot of us residents born and raised here and actually care about our land and don't hunt from a truck.

The game I go for is mostly pheasant, quail, deer. I don't like using rifles unless the season is about up and have to fill a tag. Deer season is just too dangerous on public land during rifle season so I am switching to a bow and trying to get my deer before rifle season if possible.

If there is anything else you would like to know about me just haller.

title: For Sale:  Bersa Thunder 380 CC - $300
postcontent: .380 acp semi-automatic pistol. Great starter pistol or for Concealed Carry. I have bought a different CC pistol and no longer need this one. This pistol is in great shape and has already been warranty repaired by Colorado Gun Works. These pistols have a factory problem of a spring jumping out the notch that is suppose to ride in and then fires erractically. CGW has machined the notch a little deeper and then inserted the spring and staked it off. Unlike a lot of other Bersa's out there, this one will now fire reliably when needed. Great pistol, just not needed anymore. Comes with factory box, key for integrated trigger lock, external trigger lock, factory test round, blackhawk holster, and factory magazine. One of the coolest features of this pistol is that fact that it is a Double Action/Single Action pistol with a De-cocker. This means you can breach a bullet into the chamber and then de-cock it. So then if you needed to defend yourself it will take a harder, safer, double action trigger pull to get the first round off. Then every round after that is single action. Love this feature. Alot of your smaller CC pistol are Double Action only, of which is not nearly as accurate as single action. Email if you would like to set up a meet to look at this pistol. Not interested in any "trades", other than firearms. No shotguns.

title: For Sale/Trade:  GSG-522 SD, like new + extras
postcontent:
I'm wanting to trade or possibly sell my like new GSG 522 SD.  If you're not familiar with this weapon, its a German made MP5 clone in a .22 caliber. The originals were so close in design, H&K actually sued GSG for trade dress infringement, after which there were minor cosmetic changes to the front sight and the grip. Otherwise, many aftermarket parts for MP5s are interchangeable, in addition to a mountain of forends, collapsible stocks, mag couplers, and even a 110 round drum mag available from aftermarket dealers. This rifle is bone stock, with the exception of a Tasco red dot that has been added to the factory rail. 

The rifle has had exactly one brick, 500 rounds, of clean running CCI Mini Mags through it. It likes the hotter loads, hence the "HV" (high velocity) appended to the model name on the box. The suppressor you see on the gun does not suppress the weapon, and is there to cover the legal length barrel, although making this gun suppressed and/or short barrelled is a breeze, if you have the means and your county is cool like that

 It will include one 22 round factory mag, the original box, owner's manual, tasco red dot, action padlock, chamber brush, a new .22 Boresnake, and a brand new Bulldog padded case. Also comes with about 100 rounds of mini mags and some CCI sub sonics. 

This rifle runs like a sewing machine, is cheap to shoot, and VERY accurate with the red dot or the factory diopter sight. 380.00 cash; 400.00 trade. I'm really interested in something in 5.45x39, or maybe 7.62x39 and will add cash for a good AK74 or Polish Tantal, but will entertain any and all military rifle offers, but, please, no hunting rifles or shotguns, thanks for looking.
